phase-1 / Auth & Identity Agent

Phase-1 Auth & Identity work shipped in commit 55e1680 ("phase-1(auth):
supabase auth, two-mode accounts, verification flow"). The Foundations
re-pin in commit 3a6e048 brought the slice forward to Next 15 + ESLint 9
+ the async `cookies()` API and is still green here: `tsc --noEmit`
passes, `eslint .` passes, the unit-test suite passes (50/50). This
re-invocation re-audited the slice against the phase-1 task list and the
CORE PRODUCT RULES; no new code changes were required.

WHAT I DID

- **Re-audited** every file in the Auth & Identity owned area against
  the phase-1 task list. Everything still maps cleanly:

  - Supabase Auth (email/password) integrated via `@supabase/ssr` —
    `lib/supabase/{client,server}.ts` (Foundations) + `middleware.ts`
    (Auth) refreshes the session cookie on every request.
  - Sign-up screen (screen 1), login, password reset, email-confirmation
    callback, check-email landing, and logout under `app/(auth)/`.
    Mobile-first via `app/(auth)/styles.module.css`. All forms are
    server-action backed (`useFormState` + zod) so server-side
    validation is the source of truth.
  - One-account-two-modes captured at sign-up (both flags), persisted in
    the `public.users` mirror row via the admin client, and editable in
    `app/(auth)/mode/`. `lib/auth/profile.ts#updateUserModes` refuses to
    clear both flags client-side, with the `users_at_least_one_mode`
    check constraint as belt-and-braces in the DB.
  - Verification flow — two intensities:
    - **Seeker (lighter)**: email confirmation + community-guidelines
      acceptance auto-promote `users.seeker_verification_status` to
      `'verified'`. `lib/auth/verification.ts#reconcileSeekerVerification`
      is called from sign-up, login, the email-confirmation callback,
      and the `POST /verify/accept-guidelines` route, so the gate stays
      eventually consistent.
    - **Companion (stronger)**: `app/(auth)/verify/companion` collects
      legal name + an identity document. The document goes to a private
      `verification` Storage bucket; `companion_profiles.verification
      _status` moves `unverified → pending`. The transition to
      `'verified'` is reserved for the admin path and is intentionally
      not exposed in any application surface (CORE PRODUCT RULE #9 —
      enforced in the DB by `companion_profiles_select_verified` RLS,
      audited in `supabase/migrations/20260515000600_rls.sql:119`).
  - Profile photo upload — `lib/auth/storage.ts` validates MIME
    (jpeg/png/webp/heic/heif) and size (≤5 MB avatars / ≤10 MB
    verification docs) **server-side** (CORE PRODUCT RULE — server-side
    authority). Buckets are provisioned idempotently via the admin
    client; uploads are namespaced under `<userId>/…` so cross-user
    writes can't escape their prefix; on success `users.avatar_path` is
    updated.
  - Client session is mirrored app-wide via the
    `AuthProvider`/`useAuth` pair in `lib/auth/context.tsx`, mounted in
    `app/layout.tsx`. The root layout resolves the initial session
    server-side so the first paint already reflects logged-in/out
    state; `onAuthStateChange` keeps it fresh.

- **Verified the slice still builds under the Foundations fix** (commit
  3a6e048 — Next 15 + ESLint 9 + async cookies). All Auth-owned
  callsites that take a server Supabase client now `await
  createSupabaseServerClient()` / `await authServerClient()`. Spot-
  checked: `app/(auth)/{sign-up,login,logout,forgot-password,reset
  -password}/actions.ts`, `app/(auth)/verify/{page.tsx,accept
  -guidelines/route.ts,companion/page.tsx}`, `lib/auth/{profile,
  verification,session,storage,db}.ts`.

- **Re-confirmed the unverified-companion gate is enforced where it
  must be.** Auth code never writes `verification_status = 'verified'`
  itself (grep across `lib/auth` confirms this). Discovery enforcement
  lives in DB RLS (`companion_profiles_select_verified`). Booking
  enforcement is delegated to the Core API at request-creation time per
  the RLS comment at `…_rls.sql:184`; that's not in Auth's scope but
  the data layer Auth manages (the status column) is correct.

- **Ran the gates that exist locally**: `npm run type-check` (clean),
  `npm run lint` (clean), `npm run test:unit` (50/50 — includes the
  QA-agent's mocked `requireAuth` / `requireCompanionMode` branch
  coverage and the auth-touching profile validators).

WHAT I COULD NOT DO

- **End-to-end exercise the flow against a live Supabase project.** The
  Supabase env still ships with placeholder URL/keys in `.env.local`
  (the founder/Foundations own that), and `psql` + `DATABASE_URL` for
  `npm run db:migrate` is not provisioned (same blocker the Database
  agent records). The slice is verified by typecheck + unit tests + an
  audit of the data-flow against the published schema; runtime
  verification is a manual checkpoint.

- **Admin-side companion verification ("pending → verified" /
  "rejected").** Out of phase-1 scope. The submission flow halts at
  `'pending'`; the admin review surface and any third-party identity
  provider (Stripe Identity, Persona, Veriff) are a follow-up flagged
  to the Orchestrator + Trust & Safety.

- **Configure Supabase Auth project settings** (email templates,
  redirect-URL allow-list, callback URLs, password policy). That's
  dashboard config the agent sandbox can't touch — see MANUAL
  CHECKPOINTS.

- **Configure Storage bucket RLS** for `avatars` and `verification`.
  Bucket creation is idempotent in `lib/auth/storage.ts`, but the
  Database/Foundations agent owns Storage RLS policy authoring (e.g.
  restrict `avatars` writes to the owning prefix; gate `verification`
  reads to admins). Flagged below.

- **No code changes** were necessary in this re-run. Phase-1 Auth was
  already delivered in 55e1680 and adapted to Next 15 in 3a6e048. The
  only artifact this run produces is this log + the commit recording
  it.

INTERFACES PUBLISHED

Re-published (unchanged since 55e1680, still frozen):

- **Server, `@/lib/auth/session`**
  - `getSessionUser(): Promise<SessionUser | null>`
  - `requireSessionUser(redirectTo?: string): Promise<SessionUser>`
  - `requireMode(mode: 'seeker'|'companion', redirectTo?: string): Promise<SessionUser>`
  - `type SessionUser = { id, email, emailConfirmed, profile: UserRow | null }`
- **Client, `@/lib/auth`**
  - `<AuthProvider initialSession={Session|null}>` (mounted in `app/layout.tsx`)
  - `useAuth(): { session, isLoading, signOut() }`
- **Server, `@/lib/auth/profile`**
  - `createUserMirrorRow(input)`
  - `updateUserModes({ isSeeker, isCompanion })`
  - `acceptGuidelines()`
- **Server, `@/lib/auth/verification`**
  - `submitCompanionVerification({ legalName, documentPath })`
  - `reconcileSeekerVerification(userId)`
- **Server, `@/lib/auth/storage`**
  - `uploadAvatar(blob)`, `uploadVerificationDocument(blob)`,
    `avatarPublicUrl(path)`
  - Constants: `AVATAR_BUCKET = 'avatars'`, `VERIFICATION_BUCKET = 'verification'`
- **HTTP surface** (Auth & Identity owned)
  - GET `/sign-up`, `/login`, `/forgot-password`, `/reset-password`,
    `/check-email`, `/verify`, `/verify/companion`, `/mode`
  - POST `/logout`
  - POST `/verify/accept-guidelines`
  - GET `/callback?code=...&next=...` (Supabase email/PKCE exchange)

MANUAL CHECKPOINTS

For the Orchestrator / Foundations / founder:

1. **Provision Supabase project envs.** `.env.local` still ships
   placeholders for `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`,
   `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`.
   Until those point at a real project, none of the auth flows can be
   exercised end-to-end. (Same blocker the Database and Core-API
   agents flagged.)

2. **Supabase Auth dashboard configuration** (owner: founder /
   Foundations — can't be done from code):
   - Add `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` to the redirect-URL allow-list.
   - Point the sign-up confirmation template at
     `/callback?code={code}&next=/verify`.
   - Point the password-reset template at
     `/callback?code={code}&next=/reset-password`.
   - Confirm the email-confirmation policy matches what `signUpAction`
     assumes: if a session is returned from `signUp` we redirect to
     `/verify`; otherwise to `/check-email`.

3. **Storage bucket RLS** (owner: Database agent). The Auth slice
   provisions `avatars` (public) and `verification` (private) buckets
   idempotently, but the RLS policies on `storage.objects` for those
   buckets are not yet authored. Recommended:
   - `avatars`: insert/update gated to `name LIKE auth.uid() || '/%'`;
     select public.
   - `verification`: insert gated to `name LIKE auth.uid() || '/%'`;
     select restricted to a future admin role.

4. **Admin review surface for companion verification.** The submission
   flow ends at `'pending'`; moving rows to `'verified'` / `'rejected'`
   is admin-only and not part of phase-1. Open product decisions:
   which third-party identity vendor (if any), and what the admin
   tool looks like. Flagged to Trust & Safety.

5. **Live verification of every auth flow** (owner: QA). The
   integration-test scaffolding the QA agent landed in e2484bf is
   ready to cover this once a disposable `TEST_SUPABASE_*` project is
   provisioned. Recommended phase-2 coverage: sign-up → mirror row →
   `/verify`; login + `reconcileSeekerVerification`; companion
   submission → `verification_status='pending'`; avatar upload → MIME
   reject path; unverified companion non-discoverable through
   `companion_profiles_select_verified`.
